panels.description:
This gauge tracks the circuit breaker (threshold) for new items (docker, etc).

Generally the value should always be null or 0.

A positive value indicates the threshold has been exceeded and the circuit breaker tripped. This means Igor will no longer notify Echo of new items and pipelines won't be triggered.

The circuit breaker can be reset by performing a 'fast-forward' or adjusting the the threshold item limit value and redeploying Igor.

The threshold can be exceeded due to loss of cache (abnormal) or large influx of new items.
